2.00	Xavier_Vilalta	Xavier Vilalta	Xavier Vilalta is an Catalan architect and professor. He studied Architecture between Barcelona and the United States in the Illinois Institute of Technology in Chicago. He has taught as a professor in the ETSA Barcelona School of Architecture and the Lleida University. Currently Xavier Vilalta is a research professional and an Associate Professor in ETSAB of the Polytechnic University of Catalonia. There he teaches final year design studios and mentoring diploma projects. His work has been featured in Spanish, European and international magazines and media.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/05/Xaviervilalta.jpg
